# secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.p12
*.pfx
*secret*
*token*
*credential*
# Negations: tracked infra/code whose NAME legitimately contains these words.
# (The broad globs above are a belt-and-suspenders net for secret DATA files; the
# real guard against secret CONTENT is the pre-commit scanner. NOTE for Phase 4+:
# lowercase source files like token_service.py / secret_rotation.py would be caught
# by these globs — add explicit negations for code dirs, or tighten the globs, when
# service code lands. See docs/VERSION_CONTROL.md.)
!scripts/pre-commit-secret-scan.sh
!backend/portal_tokens.py
!bin/portal_token_dry_run.py

# database and runtime state
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite3-*
*.db
*.db-*
data/
backups/
logs/
tmp/

# generated/private payloads
*.qr.png
*.qr.svg
screenshots/
uploads/
receipts/generated/
invoices/generated/

# python/runtime
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# editor/system
.DS_Store
.vscode/settings.json
